            "@type": "PropertyValue",
            "name": "reveries",
            "value": "1. The hum of the industrial steamer and the rhythmic thud of his mother's cleaver were the soundtrack to David\u2019s childhood. One evening, watching his exhausted parents painstakingly fold a hundred dumplings after closing, he felt a surge of fierce love and a silent promise \u2013 he would find a different way to ease their burden, a way to honor their sacrifice through his own achievements.\n\n2. Standing on the Berkeley campus green, acceptance letter in hand, David felt a dizzying blend of triumph and a quiet fear. He was stepping into a new, unfamiliar world, leaving behind the comforting familiarity of the Richmond District. It ignited a lifelong push to straddle worlds, balancing inherited values with personal ambition.\n\n3. That panic attack during a late-night work session, the tight chest and racing heart, was a jarring splash of cold water. It wasn't just a health scare; it was a wake-up call. He realized the relentless pursuit of external validation was eroding the very life he was building. It was the impetus for a profound shift in priorities, valuing presence over prestige.\n\n4. Watching Sarah paint in their living room, completely absorbed in her canvas, David felt a quiet awe and a sense of being truly seen. Her world of color and intuition offered a counterbalance to his structured logic, teaching him the value of vulnerability and the beauty of the unplanned. It opened his heart in ways he hadn't anticipated.\n\n5. Pedaling past the vibrant murals of the Mission on his morning commute, the crisp air filling his lungs, David feels a profound sense of belonging. This ritual isn\u2019t just exercise; it\u2019s a connection to the city\u2019s pulse, a moving meditation that grounds him and reminds him of the woven tapestry of his life \u2013 the past, the present, and the future he hopes to shape."
